<A NAME="AYRQ4201610-K_HTM_S44E1B7F9400D85F9FEFA4B454B51AB90">
</A>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:16PX;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Note&#160;6. Variable Interest Entities
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:32PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	Aircastle consolidates
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	five
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;VIEs of which it is the primary beneficiary. The operating activities of these VIEs are limited to acquiring, owning, leasing, maintaining, operating and, under certain circumstances, selling the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	seven
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;aircraft discussed below.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:16PX;PADDING-TOP:16PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Securitization
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:32PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	In May 2016, we repaid the outstanding amount plus accrued interest and fees due under our Securitization No. 2, and ACS Aircraft Finance Ireland 2 Limited became a wholly owned subsidiary of Aircastle.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:16PX;PADDING-TOP:16PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	ECA Financings
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:36PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	Aircastle, through various subsidiaries, each of which is owned by a charitable trust (such entities, collectively the &#8220;Air Knight VIEs&#8221;), has entered into
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	seven
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;different
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	twelve
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	-year term loans, which are supported by guarantees from Compagnie Francaise d&#8217; Assurance pour le Commerce Ext&#233;rieur (&#8220;COFACE&#8221;), the French government sponsored export credit agency (&#8220;ECA&#8221;). We refer to these COFACE-supported financings as &#8220;ECA Financings.&#8221;
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:32PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	Aircastle is the primary beneficiary of the Air Knight VIEs, as we have the power to direct the activities of the VIEs that most significantly impact the economic performance of such VIEs and we bear the significant risk of loss and participate in gains through a finance lease. The activity that most significantly impacts the economic performance is the leasing of aircraft of which our wholly owned subsidiary is the servicer and is responsible for managing the relevant aircraft. There is a cross collateralization guarantee between the Air Knight VIEs. In addition, Aircastle guarantees the debt of the Air Knight VIEs.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:16PX;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:32PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	The only assets that the Air Knight VIEs have on their books are financing leases that are eliminated in the consolidated financial statements. The related aircraft, with a net book value as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	December&#160;31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	$515,671
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	, were included in our flight equipment held for lease. The consolidated debt outstanding, net of debt issuance costs, of the Air Knight VIEs as of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	December&#160;31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	$296,365
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<BR>
</DIV>

<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	E - 22

<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Aircastle Limited and Subsidiaries
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Notes to Consolidated Financial Statements
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:20PX;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	(Dollars in thousands, except per share amounts)
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<BR>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:16PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Unsecured Debt Financings:
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;PADDING-TOP:16PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	DBJ Term Loan
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:30PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	In March 2016, we entered into a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	$120,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;floating rate
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	-year term loan commitment with Development Bank of Japan Inc. and certain other banks (the &#8220;DBJ Term Loan&#8221;). The loan contains a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	$750,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;minimum net worth covenant, along with other customary provisions similar to our revolving credit facilities. This loan was funded in April 2016.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Senior Notes due 2023
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:30PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	On March 21, 2016, Aircastle issued
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	$500,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;aggregate principal amount of Senior Notes due 2023. The Senior Notes due 2023 will mature on April 1, 2023 and bear interest at the rate of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	5.00%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;per annum, payable semi-annually on April 1 and October 1 of each year, commencing on October 1, 2016. Interest accrues on the Senior Notes due 2023 from March 24, 2016.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:30PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	We may redeem the Senior Notes due 2023 at any time at a redemption price equal to (a)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	100%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;of the principal amount of the notes redeemed, plus accrued and unpaid interest thereon to, but not including, the redemption date and (b) the sum of the present values of the remaining scheduled payments of principal and interest on the notes from the redemption date through the maturity date of the notes (computed using a discount rate equal to the Treasury Rate (as defined in the indenture governing the notes) as of such redemption date plus
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	50
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;basis points). In addition, prior to April 1, 2019, we may redeem up to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	40%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;of the aggregate principal amount of the notes issued under the indenture at a redemption price equal to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	105%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;plus accrued and unpaid interest thereon to, but not including, the redemption date, with the net proceeds of certain equity offerings. If the Company undergoes a change of control, it must offer to repurchase the Senior Notes due 2023 at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	101%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;of the principal amount, plus accrued and unpaid interest. The Senior Notes due 2023 are not guaranteed by any of the Company&#8217;s subsidiaries or any third party.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:30PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	Proceeds from the issuance were used to repay amounts drawn under our existing revolving credit facility and for general corporate purposes.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Revolving Credit Facilities
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:30PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	On March 29, 2016, we increased the size of our existing unsecured revolving credit facility from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	$600,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	$675,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;and extended its maturity by one year to May 2020.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:30PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	On November 21, 2016, we entered into a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	$135,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	-year, unsecured revolving credit facility with a group of banks based in Asia. This facility bears interest at a rate of LIBOR plus
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	2.1%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;and matures in November 2019. The facility contains provisions similar to our existing revolving credit facility, including a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	$750,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;minimum net worth covenant.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:30PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	At
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	December&#160;31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	, we had
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	no
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;amounts outstanding under these facilities.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:4PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:30PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">

	Aircastle Limited and Subsidiaries

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Notes to Consolidated Financial Statements
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:20PX;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	(Dollars in thousands, except per share amounts)
</FONT>

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:16PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Note&#160;8. Shareholders&#8217; Equity and Share-Based Payment
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:32PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	In January 2006, the Board of Directors (the &#8220;Board&#8221;) and shareholders managed by affiliates of Fortress Investment Group LLC (the &#8220;Fortress Shareholders&#8221;) adopted the Aircastle Investment Limited 2005 Equity and Incentive Plan, and the Board and the Fortress Shareholders approved an amendment to and restatement thereof on July&#160;20, 2006 (as so amended and restated, the &#8220;2005 Plan&#8221;).
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:30PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	On March 14, 2014, the Board of Directors adopted the Aircastle Limited 2014 Omnibus Incentive Plan (the &#8220;2014 Plan&#8221;). The 2014 Plan was approved by shareholders at the Company&#8217;s 2014 Annual General Meeting of Shareholders on May 22, 2014. The 2014 Plan replaced the 2005 Plan.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:30PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	The purposes of the 2014 Plan are to provide an additional incentive to selected officers, employees, non-employee directors, independent contractors, and consultants of the Company or its affiliates whose contributions are essential to the growth and success of the business of the Company and its affiliates, to strengthen the commitment of such persons to the Company and its affiliates, motivate such persons to faithfully and diligently perform their responsibilities and attract and retain competent and dedicated persons whose efforts will result in the long-term growth and profitability of the Company and its affiliates. To accomplish such purposes, the 2014 Plan provides that the Company may grant options, share appreciation rights, restricted shares, restricted share units, share bonuses, other share-based awards, cash awards or any combination of the foregoing. The 2014 Plan provides that grantees of restricted common shares will have all of the rights of shareholders, including the right to receive dividends, other than the right to sell, transfer, assign or otherwise dispose of the shares until the lapse of the restricted period. Generally, the restricted common shares vest over
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	five
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	-year periods based on continued service and are being expensed on a straight-line basis over the requisite service period of the awards. The terms of the grants provide for accelerated vesting under certain circumstances, including termination without cause following a change of control.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:30PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	The maximum number of Common Shares reserved for issuance under the 2014 Plan is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	2,500,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;Common Shares, which includes
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	713,540
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;Common Shares remaining under the 2005 Plan that became available for reuse following the adoption of the 2014 Plan. Restricted common shares outstanding under the 2005 Plan in the amount of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	140,887
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;shares will continue to vest subject to the terms and conditions of the 2005 Plan and the applicable awards agreements which are included in the below table.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:4PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:32PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	A summary of the fair value of non-vested restricted common shares for the years ended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	December&#160;31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	2015
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	2014
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;is as follows:
</FONT>
</DIV>

<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	The fair value of the restricted common shares granted in 2016, 2015 and 2014 were determined based upon the market price of the shares at the grant date.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:30PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	December&#160;31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	, in the amount of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	$8,986
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	, is expected to be recognized over a weighted average period of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	1.82
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;years.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:18PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Performance Share Units
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:30PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	During 2016, the Company issued performance share units (&#8220;PSUs&#8221;) to certain employees. These awards were made under the 2014 Plan. The PSUs are denominated in share units without dividend rights, each of which is equivalent to one common share, and are subject to market and performance conditions and time vesting.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:4PX;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:30PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	The PSUs granted in 2016 vest at the end of a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	-year performance period which ends on December&#160;31, 2018. Half of the PSUs vest on achieving relative total stockholder return goals (the "TSR PSUs") while the other half vest on attaining annual Adjusted Return on Equity goals (the "AROE PSUs"). The table below shows the PSU awards granted during 2016, including the number of common shares underlying the awards at the time of grant:
</FONT>
</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:30PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	The fair value of the time-based TSR PSUs was determined at the grant date using a Monte Carlo simulation model. Included in the Monte Carlo simulation model were certain assumptions regarding a number of highly complex and subjective variables, such as expected volatility, risk-free interest rate and dividend yield. To appropriately value the award, the risk-free interest rate is estimated for the time period from the valuation date until the vesting date and the historical volatilities were estimated based on a historical time frame equal to the time from the valuation date until the end date of the performance period. The number of TSR PSUs that will ultimately vest is based on the percentile ranking of the Company&#8217;s TSR among the S&amp;P Midcap 400 Index. The number of shares that will ultimately vest will range from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	0%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	200%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;of the target TSR PSUs.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;PADDING-TOP:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:30PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	The number of shares vesting from the AROE PSUs at the end of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	-year performance period will depend on the Company&#8217;s Adjusted Return on Equity as measured against the targets set by the Compensation Committee annually during the performance period, consistent with the business plan approved by the Board. The maximum number of AROE PSUs for 2016 is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	95,607
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	. The fair value of the 2016 AROE PSUs was determined based on the closing market price of the Company&#8217;s common shares on the date of grant reduced by the present value of expected dividends to be paid. The number of shares that will ultimately vest will range from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	0%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	200%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;of the target AROE PSUs.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:30PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	During
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	, the Company granted a target of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	191,216
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;PSUs of which
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	143,414
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;are TSR PSUs and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	47,802
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;are AROE PSUs. The remaining
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	95,607
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;of target AROE PSUs will be considered granted upon the Compensation Committee&#8217;s setting the target AROE for the respective period. The following table summarizes the activities for our unvested PSUs for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:30PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	$1,261
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	$3,251
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&#32;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	of unrecognized compensation cost related to unvested PSUs granted to certain employees that is expected to be recognized over a weighted-average remaining period of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	2.0 years
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-LEFT:4PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:30PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	Under the repurchase program approved by the Company&#8217;s Board of Directors on February 9, 2016, the Company may purchase its common shares from time to time in the open market or in privately negotiated transactions. During 2016, we repurchased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	1,868,352
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	$35,191
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	, including commissions. As of December 31, 2016, the remaining dollar value of common shares that may be purchased under the current repurchase program is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	$95,888
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	. We also repurchased
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	102,927
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;shares totaling
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	$2,150
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;from our employees and directors to settle tax obligations related to share vesting.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-LEFT:4PX;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:30PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">

<A NAME="AYRQ4201610-K_HTM_S470A8211D298EA2A99004B454B9713C2">
</A>

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:16PX;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Note&#160;10. Earnings Per Share
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:32PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	We include all common shares granted under our incentive compensation plan which remain unvested (&#8220;restricted common shares&#8221;) and contain non-forfeitable rights to dividends or dividend equivalents, whether paid or unpaid (&#8220;participating securities&#8221;), in the number of shares outstanding in our basic and diluted EPS calculations using the two-class method. All of our restricted common shares are currently participating securities. Our PSUs are contingently issuable shares which are included in our diluted earnings per share calculations which do not include voting or dividend rights.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:32PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	Under the two-class method, earnings per common share are computed by dividing the sum of distributed earnings allocated to common shareholders and undistributed earnings allocated to common shareholders by the weighted average number of common shares outstanding for the period. In applying the two-class method, distributed and undistributed earnings are allocated to both common shares and restricted common shares based on the total weighted average shares outstanding during the period as follows:
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:32PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:32PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV>
<BR>
</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	E - 27
</FONT>

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:16PX;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Note&#160;11. Income Taxes
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:32PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	Income taxes have been provided for based upon the tax laws and rates in countries in which our operations are conducted and income is earned. The Company received an assurance from the Bermuda Minister of Finance that it would be exempted from local income, withholding and capital gains taxes until March 2035. Consequently, the provision for income taxes relates to income earned by certain subsidiaries of the Company which are located in, or earn income in, jurisdictions that impose income taxes, primarily Ireland, Singapore and the United States.
</FONT>
</DIV>

	, or

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;per diluted common share. Deferred tax assets and liabilities are included in Other assets and Accounts payable and accrued liabilities, respectively, in the accompanying Consolidated Balance Sheets.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:32PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	We do not expect to incur income taxes on future distributions of undistributed earnings of non-U.S.&#160;subsidiaries and accordingly, no deferred income taxes have been provided for the distributions of such earnings. As of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;COLOR:#000000;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	December&#160;31, 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;we have elected to permanently reinvest our accumulated undistributed U.S.&#160;earnings of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	$10,899
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	. Accordingly, no U.S.&#160;withholding taxes have been provided. Withholding tax of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	$3,270
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	&#32;would be due if such earnings were remitted.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:32PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	All of our aircraft-owning subsidiaries that are recognized as corporations for U.S.&#160;tax purposes are non-U.S.&#160;corporations. These non-U.S.&#160;subsidiaries generally earn income from sources outside the United States and typically are not subject to U.S.&#160;federal, state or local income taxes unless they operate within the U.S., in which case they may be subject to federal, state and local income taxes. The aircraft owning subsidiaries resident in Ireland, Mauritius and Singapore are subject to tax in those respective jurisdictions.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:32PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	We have a U.S-based subsidiary which provides management services to our non-U.S.&#160;subsidiaries and is subject to U.S.&#160;federal, state and local income taxes. We also have Ireland and Singapore based subsidiaries which provide management services to our non-U.S. subsidiaries and are subject to tax in those respective jurisdictions.
</FONT>
</DIV>

<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	The Company recognizes the tax benefit from an uncertain tax position only if it is more likely than not that the tax position will be sustained on examination by the taxing authorities. We did not have any unrecognized tax benefits.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:32PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	We conduct business globally and, as a result, the Company and its subsidiaries or branches are subject to foreign, U.S.&#160;federal and various state and local income taxes, as well as withholding taxes. In the normal course of business the Company is subject to examination by taxing authorities throughout the world, including such major jurisdictions as Ireland and the United States. With few exceptions, the Company and its subsidiaries or branches remain subject to examination for all periods since inception.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:16PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:32PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	Our policy is that we will recognize interest and penalties accrued on any unrecognized tax benefits as a component of income tax expense. We did not accrue interest or penalties associated with any unrecognized tax benefits, nor was any interest expense or penalty recognized during the year.
</FONT>
</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:16PX;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Note&#160;13. Commitments and Contingencies
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:12PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:32PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	Rent expense, primarily for the corporate office and sales and marketing facilities, was approximately

</FONT>

	$2,283
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">

	70%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	&#32;of our floating rate interest exposure. The interest rate cap is set at
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	2%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	&#32;and has a starting notional balance of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	$430,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	&#32;and reduces over time to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	$215,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	. The cap matures in September 2021. The fair value of the interest rate cap was $
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">
	5,735
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:8PT;">

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:16PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Note 15. Accounts Payable, Accrued Expenses and Other Liabilities
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:4PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:32PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	The following table describes the principal components of accounts payable, accrued expenses and other liabilities recorded on our Consolidated Balance Sheets as of:
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:16PX;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
<DIV STYLE="PADDING-LEFT:0PX;TEXT-INDENT:0PX;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;PADDING-TOP:10PX;">
<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;WIDTH:100%;BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;">

<TD COLSPAN="8">
</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:75%;">
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:1%;">
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:10%;">
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:1%;">
</TD>

<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	AMENDMENT No. 2 TO
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	PURCHASE AGREEMENT COM0270-15
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:16PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	This Amendment No. 2 COM0727-16 (the &#8220;Amendment No. 2&#8221;) dated as of November 11, 2016 is between Embraer S.A. (&#8220;Embraer&#8221;) and Aircastle Holding Corporation Limited (&#8220;Buyer&#8221;), collectively referred to herein as the &#8220;Parties&#8221;, and constitutes an amendment and modification to Purchase Agreement COM0270-15 dated June 22, 2016 as amended from time to time (the &#8220;Purchase Agreement&#8221;).
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:16PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	All capitalized terms not otherwise defined herein shall have the same meaning when used herein as provided in the Purchase Agreement and in case of any conflict between this Amendment No. 2 and the Purchase Agreement, this Amendment No. 2 shall control.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:16PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	WHEREAS
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	, [***];
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:16PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	NOW, THEREFORE, for good and valuable consideration, which is hereby acknowledged by the Parties, Embraer and Buyer agree as follows:
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:16PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	1. CONFIGURATION CHANGES TO THE AIRCRAFT
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:16PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	[***]
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:16PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	2. ATTACHMENT CHANGE
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:16PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	As a result of the changes referred to in Article 1 above, the Attachment &#8220;A1&#8221; and Attachment &#8220;A2&#8221; to the Purchase Agreement are hereby deleted and replaced in their entirety by the Attachment &#8220;A1&#8221; and Attachment &#8220;A2&#8221; to this Amendment No. 2, which shall be deemed to be Attachment &#8220;A1&#8221; and Attachment &#8220;A2&#8221; for all purposes under the Purchase Agreement.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:16PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	3. REINSTATEMENT OF PURCHASE AGREEMENT
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-TOP:16PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	All other provisions and conditions of the referenced Purchase Agreement, as well as its related Attachments, which are not specifically modified by this Amendment No. 2 shall remain in full force and effect without any change.
</FONT>
</DIV>

<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	AMENDMENT No. 3 TO
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	PURCHASE AGREEMENT COM0270-15
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	This Amendment No. 3 to the Purchase Agreement COM0270-15, dated as of January 13
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<SUP STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP;LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:PT">
	th
</SUP>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	, 2017 (&#8220;Amendment No. 3&#8221;) relates to the Purchase Agreement COM0270-15 (the &#8220;Purchase Agreement&#8221;) between Embraer S.A. (&#8220;Embraer&#8221;) and Aircastle Holding Corporation Limited (&#8220;Buyer&#8221;) dated June 12
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<SUP STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP;LINE-HEIGHT:120%;FONT-SIZE:PT">
	th
</SUP>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	, 2015 (the &#8220;Agreement&#8221;). This Amendment No. 3 is between Embraer and Buyer, collectively referred to herein as the &#8220;Parties&#8221;.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;PADDING-LEFT:24PX;TEXT-INDENT:-24PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	This Amendment No. 3 sets forth additional agreements between Embraer and Buyer with respects to the matters set forth herein.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;PADDING-LEFT:24PX;TEXT-INDENT:-24PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	Except as otherwise provided for herein, all terms of the Purchase Agreement shall remain in full force and effect. All capitalized terms used in this Amendment No. 3 which are not defined herein shall have the meaning given in the Purchase Agreement. In the event of any conflict between this Amendment No. 3 and the Purchase Agreement, the terms, conditions and provisions of this Amendment No. 3 shall control.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;PADDING-LEFT:24PX;TEXT-INDENT:-24PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	WHEREAS,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	Buyer has requested and Embraer agrees that the Contractual Delivery Date shall be amended.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	NOW, THEREFORE
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	, for good and valuable consideration which is hereby acknowledged, Embraer and Buyer hereby agree as follows:
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	1. DELIVERY
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	The Attachment &#8220;E&#8221; to the Purchase Agreement is hereby deleted and replaced in its entirety by the Attachment &#8220;E&#8221; to this Amendment No. 3.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;PADDING-LEFT:26PX;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">

</FONT>

	2. PAYMENT
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	[***]
</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	3. ATTACHMENT CHANGE
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<BR>
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	As a result of the changes referred to in Article 1 above, the Attachment &#8220;E&#8221; to the Purchase Agreement is hereby deleted and replaced in their entirety by the Attachment &#8220;E&#8221; to this Amendment No. 3, which shall be deemed to be Attachment &#8220;E&#8221; for all purposes under the Purchase Agreement.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;PADDING-TOP:16PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">

	4. REINSTATEMENT OF PURCHASE AGREEMENT
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;PADDING-TOP:8PX;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:INHERIT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
	All other provisions and conditions of the referenced Purchase Agreement, as well as its related Attachments, which are not specifically modified by this Amendment No. 3 shall remain in full force and effect without any change.
</FONT>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="LINE-HEIGHT:120%;PADDING-BOTTOM:8PX;PADDING-TOP:16PX;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;FONT-SIZE:10.5PT;">
